Dhanajaya Singh (Windows Engineer): Manages Windows agent deployment, Sysmon integration, and Microsoft environment telemetry.

üõ†Ô∏è Week 1: Infrastructure Milestones
During this initial phase, the team successfully established the "brain" of our security operations.

1. SOC Manager Deployment
Platform: Deployed Wazuh (v4.7.2) using Docker on a Kali Linux host.

Service Conflict Resolution: Successfully identified and resolved a port conflict where the local Apache service was blocking the Wazuh Dashboard on port 443.

Security Configuration: Hardened the dashboard access with custom credentials and successfully verified the Indexer, Manager, and Dashboard health.

2. First Agent Enrollment (The Lead Node)
Host: Kali Linux (IP: 192.168.204.129).

Status: Active.

Telemetry: The agent is now actively forwarding security telemetry, including logs and system inventory, to the central manager.

3. Repository Integrity
GitHub Sync: Resolved folder structure issues and subproject commit errors to ensure all configuration files are accessible for review.

Configuration: All YAML and environment files for the single-node deployment are securely documented within the repository.

