üõ°Ô∏è What We Accomplished in Week 1
1. SOC Infrastructure Orchestration
We successfully deployed the Wazuh Manager, Indexer, and Dashboard using a containerized Docker architecture. This provides an isolated "Command Center" for the Sentient Shield that can handle telemetry from hundreds of machines.

2. Technical Troubleshooting (The Apache Fix)
We faced a real-world infrastructure hurdle where the local Apache service was blocking port 443. You successfully identified this conflict, stopped the conflicting service, and reconfigured the network to allow the Wazuh Dashboard to go live.

3. Establishing the Communication Grid
We configured the environment so the Manager listens at your primary static IP: 192.168.204.129. This IP is now the central "Beacon" for all future agents in the Infotact Solutions network.

4. Moving to "Active" Status (The First Eye)
By enrolling your Kali machine, you moved the "Total Agents" count from 0 to 1.

What it is doing now: Your agent is currently performing Log Data Analysis, File Integrity Monitoring (FIM), and Vulnerability Scans on your local machine.

Why it matters: Your system is no longer just a "view"; it is now actively collecting security telemetry.

5. GitHub Repository Integrity
We fixed the "404 Error" and "Subproject Commit" issues. By converting wazuh-docker from a submodule to a normal directory, your code is now fully transparent and professional for project review.
